Petition—Marriage/Domestic Partnership
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Start a divorce, legal separation, or annulment case if you are married, registered domestic partners, or both.  This identifies all the issues you want to include in a judgment.

Form name: Declaration Under Uniform Child Custody Jurisdiction and Enforcement Act (UCCJEA)
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity, Guardianship, Divorce or Separation, Domestic Violence, Restraining Order

Form name: Attachment to Declaration Under Uniform Child Custody Jurisdiction and Enforcement Act (UCCJEA)
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity, Guardianship

Form name: Legal Steps for a Divorce or Legal Separation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explains the steps to begin and complete a case for divorce or legal separation. It includes links to online resources to help understand each step in the process.

Form name: Summons
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells your spouse or domestic partner that a court case has started and what will happen if a response is not filed in 30 days.

Form name: Proof of Service of Summons (Uniform Parentage-Custody and Support)
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity, Divorce or Separation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells the court that you had your spouse or domestic partner served with the legal papers to start your case. Tells when and where the papers were served, and who served them.

Form name: Notice and Acknowledgment of Receipt
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court that your spouse or domestic partner agreed to (and received) by mail the legal papers to start your case.

Form name: Response—Marriage/Domestic Partnership
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court and your spouse or domestic partner that you are responding to the summons and petition and describe the orders you want the court to make in the case.

Form name: Appearance, Stipulations, and Waivers (Uniform Parentage—Custody and Support)
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Divorce or Separation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court that you and your spouse or domestic partner want the court to approve your written agreement or stipulated judgment without going to court for a trial.

Form name: Declaration and Conditional Waiver of Rights Under the Servicemembers Civil Relief Act of 2003
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court you are a servicemember on active duty and you want the court to enter your settlement agreement or stipulated judgment in your absence.

Form name: Declaration of Disclosure
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: List all the financial documents and information on this cover page that you give (disclose) to your spouse or domestic partner as part of the first or final set of disclosure documents.

Form name: Declaration Regarding Service of Declaration of Disclosure and Income and Expense Declaration
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court that you had the first or final set of financial documents served on your spouse or domestic partner.

Form name: Schedule of Assets and Debts
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: v. 1 List all your known property and debt. This can be used as an attachment to Declaration of Disclosure (form FL-140) or you may use Property Declaration (form FL-160) instead. (see notes for v2)

Form name: Stipulation and Waiver of Final Declaration of Disclosure
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court that you and your spouse or domestic partner exchanged the preliminary (first) declaration of disclosure and agree not to exchange the final declaration of disclosure documents with each other.

Form name: Form Interrogatories—Family Law
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell your spouse or domestic partner to answer specific questions and give documents before trial.

Form name: Income and Expense Declaration
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity, Divorce or Separation, Domestic Violence, Restraining Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Give your financial information to the court and to your spouse or domestic partner.  The court uses the information to make orders for support, attorneys fees, and other costs.

Form name: Financial Statement (Simplified)
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity, Domestic Violence, Restraining Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Give your financial information to the court and to your spouse or domestic partner. This also explains when to use either this form or form FL-150. The court considers the information before making child support orders.

Form name: Spousal or Partner Support Declaration Attachment
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explain the facts that support your request for a spousal or domestic partner support judgment. This is always attached to another form, like Declaration for Default or Uncontested Judgment (Form FL-170)

Form name: Supporting Declaration for Attorney's Fees and Costs Attachment
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explain why the court should or should not order you or your spouse or domestic partner to pay attorneys fees and costs. This is always attached to Request for Attorney's Fees and Costs Attachment (form FL-319) or Responsive Declaration (form FL-320).

Form name: Property Declaration
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: List your property and debts.  This can be used as an attachment to Declaration of Disclosure (form FL-140) or you may use Schedule of Assets and Debts (form FL-142) instead.

Form name: Continuation of Property Declaration
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Give more details about your propery and debts and attach to Property Declaration (form FL-160)

Form name: Request to Enter Default (Uniform Parentage)
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Parentage/Paternity, Divorce or Separation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Ask the court for a decision (order) that time has ended for your spouse or domestic partner to file a response to your petition. This allows you to ask the court for a judgment based on a signed settlement agreement or, if no agreement, based on what you asked for in the petition.

Form name: Declaration for Default or Uncontested Dissolution or Legal Separation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court more about your request to enter a judgment based on an agreement or the default of your spouse or domestic partner.

Form name: Case Information—Family Law
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Used by courts to specify important issues in a family law case.

Form name: Family Centered Case Resolution Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Used by courts to provide a record of decisions made during a family centered case resolution conference.

Form name: Judgment
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: The first pages of the final orders for your divorce, legal separation, or annulment case. You or your attorney complete the first page and use attachments for other final orders, like child custody and visitation, child support, spousal or domestic partner support, property division, attorneys fees, and other orders.

Form name: Judgment Checklist—Dissolution/Legal Separation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: This cover page lists the documents you give to the court to ask for a default or uncontested judgment.

Form name: Notice of Entry of Judgment (Uniform Parentage—Custody and Support)
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Parentage/Paternity, Divorce or Separation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Lists the type of judgment that the court made (granted), like divorce, legal separation, or annulment. It also states the date that your legal relationship changed and the date that the court entered the judgment.

Form name: Child Support Case Registry Form
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity, Divorce or Separation, Domestic Violence, Restraining Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Give information to the court about the child support or family support order in your case.

Form name: Notice of Rights and Responsibilities (Health-Care Costs and Reimbursement Procedures)
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity, Divorce or Separation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explains how to ask the other parent to help pay for your child's health care cost that is not covered by insurance. It also describes how to change a child support order.

Form name: Income Withholding for Support
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity, Divorce or Separation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells an employer that the court made an order for you or the other person in the case to pay child support, medical support, spousal or domestic partner support (and any past-due support). The order tells the employer how much money to take out of the employee's pay check, how often to take out the money, and where to send it. This is also known as a wage assignment.

Form name: Income Withholding for Support—Instructions
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity, Divorce or Separation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explains how to fill out Income Withholding for Support (form FL-195). Also includes information for the employer.

Form name: Petition to Establish Parental Relationship (Uniform Parentage)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Start a case to get a court order (judgment) that identifies the legal parents of a child. This is used by parents who are not married.

Form name: Summons (Uniform Parentage—Petition for Custody and Support) (incl. Spanish)
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells the other parent of the child that a court case has started and what will happen if the other parent's response is not filed in 30 days.

Form name: Response to Petition to Establish Parental Relationship (Uniform Parentage)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court and your spouse or domestic partner that you are responding to the summons and petition and describe the orders that you want the court to make in the case.

Form name: Declaration for Default or Uncontested Judgment (Uniform Parentage—Custody and Support)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Use this with Request for Default (form FL-165) to ask the court for a decision (order) that time has ended for the other parent to file a response to your petition. This allows you to ask the court for a judgment based on a signed settlement agreement or, if no agreement, based on what you asked for in the petition.

Form name: Advisement and Waiver of Rights Re: Establishment of Parental Relationship (Uniform Parentage)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court that you and the other parent have an agreement to establish parentage and that you agree to give up the rights listed in the form so that the court can approve the Judgment (form FL-250) without a trial.

Form name: Stipulation for Entry of Judgment Re: Establishment of Parental Relationship (Uniform Parentage)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: This is the first page of the agreement you have with the child's other parent about establishing parentage, child custody and visitation (parenting time), child support, and other matters.

Form name: Judgment (Uniform Parentage—Custody and Support)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: The first pages of the final orders (judgment) that establish the legal parents of child. You or your attorney complete this and use attachments for other final orders, like child custody and visitation, (parenting time). child support, and others.

Form name: Petition for Custody and Support of Minor Children
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support

Form name: Response to Petition for Custody and Support of Minor Children
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court and the petitioner that you are responding to the summons and petition and describe the orders that you want the court to make in the case.

Form name: Notice of Motion to Set Aside Judgment of Paternity (Governmental)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court and the other parent that you want a hearing to ask the court to cancel all the orders included in the judgment of parentage. Also ask the court to order genetic testing and enter a judgment stating that you are not the child's parent.

Form name: Declaration in Support of Motion to Set Aside Judgment of Paternity (Governmental)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Give more information about your request to cancel a judgment of parentage. This must be attached to Notice of Motion to Cancel (Set Aside) Judgment of Parentage (form F-272).

Form name: Information Sheet for Completing Notice of Motion to Set Aside Judgment of Paternity (Governmental)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explains who can ask the court to cancel a judgment of parentage, what forms are needed, and desribes the time frame for the filing.

Form name: Response to Notice of Motion to Set Aside Judgment of Paternity (Governmental)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court and the other parties if you agree or disagree with the orders the other party asked for in Notice of Motion to Cancel (Set Aside) Judgment of Parentage (form FL-272).  Also give facts to support your response.

Form name: Order After Hearing on Motion to Set Aside Judgment of Paternity (Governmental)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision (an order) about the request to cancel (set aside) a judgment of parentage.

Form name: Request for Hearing and Application to Set Aside Voluntary Declaration of Paternity (Governmental)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court and the other parties that you want a hearing to ask the court to cancel (set aside) the voluntary declaration of parentage or paternity. This is also used by the court to set the date, time, and location of the hearing.

Form name: Information Sheet for Completing Request for Hearing and Application to Set Aside Voluntary Declaration of Paternity (Governmental)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explains how to complete Request for Hearing and Application to Cancel (Set Aside) Voluntary Declaration of Parentage or Paternity (form FL-280) and describes the timeframe for filing the form.

Form name: Responsive Declaration to Application to Set Aside Voluntary Declaration of Paternity (Governmental)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court and the other parties if you agree or disagree with the orders the other party asked for in Request for Hearing on Motion to Cancel (Set Aside) Voluntary Declaration of Parentage (form FL-280). Also give facts to support your response.

Form name: Order After Hearing on Motion to Set Aside Voluntary Declaration of Paternity (Governmental)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision (an order) about the request to cancel (set aside) a voluntary declaration of parentage or paternity.

Form name: Request for Order
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Divorce or Separation, Domestic Violence, Restraining Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Ask the court to make decisions (orders) about specific issues in your family law case. This is also used by the court to set the date, time, and location of the hearing.

Form name: Information Sheet for Request for Order
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Divorce or Separation, Domestic Violence, Restraining Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explains how to fill out Request for Order (form FL-300) to ask the court to make decisions (orders) in your family law case. It includes: steps to get a hearing date on the court's regular calendar or ask for emergency orders, information about serving the papersparty served, and resources if you have questions or need legal help.

Form name: Declaration Regarding Notice and Service of Request for Temporary Emergency (Ex Parte) Orders
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells the court if and how you let the other party know that you are asking the court to make emergency orders in your case. You can also use the form to ask the court to order that notice is not needed before the court makes emergency orders.

Form name: Temporary Emergency (Ex Parte) Orders
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision (order) when a party asked for temporary emergency orders.

Form name: Request to Continue Hearing
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Ask to change your hearing date and explain why you need a new hearing date.

Form name: Order on Request to Continue Hearing
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision (order) when a party asked to change a hearing date.

Form name: Child Custody and Visitation (Parenting Time) Application Attachment
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Divorce or Separation, Domestic Violence, Restraining Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Give the court and the other party more details about the orders you want the court to make about child custody and visitation (parenting time).

Form name: Request for Child Abduction Prevention Orders
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court why you are worried that the other parent might kidnap your child and ask for orders to try to prevent that from happening.

Form name: Child Custody Information Sheet—Recommending Counseling
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explains that some family courts use child custody recommending counseling (CCRC) to help parents create a parening plan agreement before the court makes orders about child custody and visitation. This form also explains the next steps if parents do not agree on a parenting plan during CCRC and includes information about how to find help.

Form name: Child Custody Information Sheet—Child Custody Mediation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explains that family courts uses mediation to help parents create their own parenting plan agreement before the court makes orders about child custody and visitation. This form also explains the next steps if parents do not agree on a parenting plan and includes information about how to find help.

Form name: Request or Response to Request for Separate Trial
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Ask the court for a trial to decide one important issue before all other issues in your case. This can also be used to respond to a request for separate trial.

Form name: Request for Orders Regarding Noncompliance With Disclosure Requirements
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court that you gave the other party a complete declaration of disclosure as required by law, but the other party did not do the same. Then, list the orders that you want the court to make. This form is always attached to Request for Order (form FL-300).

Form name: Retirement Plan Joinder—Information Sheet
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Lists different types of retirement plans and tells you if the plan, by law, needs to be joined (made a party to the case) before the court makes orders that change your legal status and divide the retirement plan.

Form name: Request for Attorney's Fees and Costs Attachment
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Give the court and the other party more details about the order for attorney's fees that you are asking the court to make.

Form name: Responsive Declaration to Request for Order
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Divorce or Separation, Domestic Violence, Restraining Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court and the other party if you agree or disagree with the orders the other party asked for in Request for Order (form FL-300).  Also describe the orders you want the court to make instead of those that the other party asked for.

Form name: Information Sheet: Responsive Declaration to Request for Order
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explains how to complete Responsive Declaration to Request for Order (form FL-320), file, and have it served.

Form name: Witness List
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Ask the court to allow each person that you list to testify (give evidence in person) at a hearing or trial.  You must also describe what each person is expected to say to the court.

Form name: Declaration of Counsel for a Child Regarding Qualifications
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells you and the court that the lawyer is qualified to represent a child in the case. This is used by a lawyer to specify the licenses, professional liability insurance, education and training, experience, annual continuing education that satsify the requirements for appointment.

Form name: Order Appointing Counsel for a Child
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision (an order) to appoint a lawyer for your child. Also states the lawyer's rights and responsibilities and how the lawyer will be paid.

Form name: Attorney for Child in a Family Law Case—Information Sheet
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: This answers general questions about lawyers appointed for a child in a family law case.  Questions include: What will the lawyer do?  Who pays the lawyer?  How long will the lawyer represent the child?

Form name: Declaration of Supervised Visitation Provider
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells you and the court that the person is eligible to be appointed by the court as a paid (professional) or unpaid (nonprofessional) supervised visitation provider. This lists the provider's specific qualifications and says that the person satisfies the appointment requirements.

Form name: Declaration of Court-connected Child Custody Evaluator Regarding Qualifications
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells you and the court that the person is a court employee who is eligible to be appointed to as a child custody evaluator.  This is used to list the employee's specific qualifications before the court orders the appointment.

Form name: Declaration of Private Child Custody Evaluator Regarding Qualifications
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells you and the court that the person is a private professional who is eligible to be appointed to as a child custody evaluator.  This is used to list the person's specific qualifications before the court orders the appointment.

Form name: Order Appointing Child Custody Evaluator
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision (an order) to appoint a licensed psychologist, marriage and family therapist, clinical social worker, or psychiatrist to investigate and make recommendations about child custody and visitation orders that are in your child's best interest.

Form name: Notice Regarding Confidentiality of Child Custody Evaluation Report
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: The child custody evaluator uses this as the first page of the written recommendations for child cusody and a parenting plan in your case. This explains that the recommendation must be kept confidential, lists the exceptions to confidentiality, and warns about penalties for disclosing the report against the child's best interests.

Form name: Child Custody Evaluation Information Sheet
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Gives general information to parents when the court appoints a child custody evaluator to make recommendations about a parenting plan that is in the child's best interest.

Form name: Proof of Personal Service
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity, Divorce or Separation, Domestic Violence, Restraining Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells the court that you had the other party served in person with legal papers.  Lists the papers that were served. It also tells when and where the papers were served and who served them.

Form name: Information Sheet for Proof of Personal Service
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity, Divorce or Separation, Domestic Violence, Restraining Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explains who can serve legal documents and how to complete Proof of Personal Service (form FL-330)

Form name: Declaration Regarding Address Verification—Postjudgment Request to Modify a Child Custody, Visitation, or Child Support Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells the court that you are certain of the address where the other parent lives and that you had the other parent served by mail at that address with a Request for Order (form FL-300) to change a judgment or permanent orders for child custody, visitation, or child support. This is used as an attachment to a proof of service by mail.

Form name: Proof of Service by Mail
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity, Divorce or Separation, Domestic Violence, Restraining Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells the court that you had the other party served legal papers buy mail.  Lists the papers that were served and tells when and where the papers were served, as well as who served them.

Form name: Information Sheet for Proof of Service by Mail
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity, Divorce or Separation, Domestic Violence, Restraining Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explains how to complete Proof of Service by Mail (form FL-335). Also explains who can serve legal papers by mail and which legal papers cannot be served by mail.

Form name: Order to Pay Waived Court Fees and Costs (Superior Court)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision (an order) that a party must pay back the initial fees that the court previously waived (said that the party did not have to pay). Also explains how to ask the court to continue to waive those fees.

Form name: Application to Set Aside Order to Pay Waived Court Fees—Attachment
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court and the other person in your case that you want the court to continue the order to waive the initial fees in your case. This form is always attached to Request for Order (form FL-300).

Form name: Order After Hearing on Motion to Set Aside Order to Pay Waived Court Fees (Superior Court)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision (an order) when a party asks the court to continue waiving the initial fees in the family law case.

Form name: Findings and Order After Hearing
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Divorce or Separation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: v1 This is used as the first page to list the decisions (orders) that a court made after a hearing. The orders are generally attached to this page.                          v2. This is used as the first page of the decisions (orders) that the court made after a hearing about child custody and visitation (parenting time), child support, spousal or domestic partner support, property, attorney's fees, or other matters. The actual orders are generally attached to this page.

Form name: Child Custody and Visitation (Parenting Time) Order Attachment
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity, Divorce or Separation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decisions (orders) after a hearing about child custody and visitation (parenting time) plans that are in the child's best interest. This can be used as an attachment to many other forms, as noted at the top of form FL-341.

Form name: Supervised Visitation Order
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decisions (orders) after a hearing about supervised visitation (parenting time) or supervised exchanges. This is attached to Child Custody and Visitation (Parenting Time) Order Attachment (form FL-341).

Form name: Child Abduction Prevention Order Attachment
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decisions (order) after a hearing on whether a child is at risk of being kidnapped by a parent. The orders are generally attached to Child Custody and Visitation (Parenting Time) Order Attachment (form FL-341) or Custody Order--Juvenile--Final Judgment (form JV-200).

Form name: Children's Holiday Schedule Attachment
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: This can be used as an attachment to many forms. Parents can use the form to describe the holiday parenting plan believed to be in the child's best interests. It can also be used to state the family or juvenile court's decisions (orders) about the child's holiday parenting plan after a hearing.

Form name: Additional Provisions—Physical Custody Attachment
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: This can be used as an attachment to many forms.  Parents can use the form to make agreements, or request court orders, about other matters concerning child custody that are in the child's best interest. It can also be used to state family or juvenile court's decisions (orders) about additional child custody issues.

Form name: Joint Legal Custody Attachment
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: This can be used as an attachment to many forms.  Parents can use the form to make agreements, or request court orders, about how parents will exercise joint legal custody in the child's best interest. It can also be used to state the family or juvenile court's decisions (orders) about additional child custody issues.

Form name: Child Support Information and Order Attachment
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity, Divorce or Separation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decisions (orders) about child support. This can be attached to many other forms, including Findings and Order After Hearing (form FL-340), Judgments (forms FL-180 and FL-250), and Restraining Order After Hearing (form DV -130).

Form name: Non-Guideline Support Findings Attachment
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's reasons why it decided (ordered), or the parent's agreed to, child support payments  that are below or above the statewide child support guidelines. This is generally attached to Child Support Information and Order Attachment (form FL-342) or Judgment (form FL-180).

Form name: Spousal, Partner, or Family Support Order Attachment
Case types: Divorce or Separation, Domestic Violence, Restraining Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision (order or judgment), or the parties' agreement, about spousal, domestic partner, or family support.

Form name: Property Order Attachment to Findings and Order After Hearing
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decisions (orders) about the parties' assets and debts. This is attached to Findings and Orde After Hearing (form FL-340).

Form name: Property Order Attachment to Judgment
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decisions about the division of the parties' assets and debts. This is attached to a judgment.

Form name: Attorney's Fees and Costs Order Attachment
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision (an order) about who will pay attorney's fees and cost, the amount of each payment, and when payments are due. This is attached to Findings and Order After Hearing (form FL-340), Judgment (form FL-180 or FL-250), or another document.

Form name: Bifurcation of Status of Marriage or Domestic Partnership—Attachment
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decisions (orders) about the date the parties are to become legally single and other orders that are connected to the change of legal status.

Form name: Pension Benefits—Attachment to Judgment (Attach to form FL-180)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells the pension plan administrator that court made temporary orders about the pension until a final order (a qualified domestic relations order) is completed.  Explains what parties need to do to protect their interest in the pension.

Form name: Stipulation to Establish or Modify Child Support and Order
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Parents tell the court about their agreement to make an initial (the first) orders for child support or modify (change) existing orders. The court also uses this to make their agreement a court order.

Form name: Stipulation and Order for Custody and/or Visitation of Children
Case types: Custody and Parenting Time (Visitation), Child Support, Parentage/Paternity
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Parents tell the court that they have an agreement about child custody and visitation (parenting time) and that the agreement is attach to the form. The court also uses this to make their agreement a  court order.

Form name: Confidential Request for Special Immigrant Juvenile Findings—Family Law
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court and the other parties that you are asking the court for a hearing to give you sole physical custody of the child and make certain findings (conclusions) about the child. Give the court information and documents to support your request for the court to make findings about child custody and make other findings that state (1) it is not legally possible to return the child to the other parent due to abuse, neglect, abandonment, or another legal reason and (2) it is not in the child's best interest to return to the parent's or the child's country of nationality or habitual residence.

Form name: Special Immigrant Juvenile Findings
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's findings (conclusions) after considering facts and evidence included with a Confidential Request for Special Immigrant Juvenile Findings (form FL-355)

Form name: Confidential Response to Request for Special Immigrant Juvenile Findings
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court and the other party if you agree or disagree with the findings that the other party requested in form FL-356.  Also,if applicable, describe the findings that you would want the court to make instead of those that the other party asked for.

Form name: Request for Hearing and Application to Set Aside Support Order Under Family Code Section 3691
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court and the other party that the court should dismiss (set-aside") an order that requires you to pay support. The grounds for setting aside a support order are: fraud
Arabic URL: or lack of notice. You must also file the request by the time specified in the form."

Form name: Responsive Declaration to Application to Set Aside Support Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court and the other party or parties whether or not you agree to dismiss (set-aside) the support order and give your reasons.

Form name: Order After Hearing on Motion to Set Aside Support Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision (an order) after a hearing about a party's request to dismiss (set-aside") a support order based on fraud

Form name: Pleading on Joinder—Employees Benefit Plan
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells an employee benefit plan administrator that the plan has been made a claiment (a party) to the court case.

Form name: Notice of Motion and Declaration for Joinder
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Ask the court to decide (order) to make you a party in the family law case. This is commonly used by a grandparent or a step-parent who wants to participate in the case concerning child custody and visitation (parenting time).

Form name: Request for Joinder of Employee Benefit Plan Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court that you want an order for the administrator of an employee benefit plan to become party in the case. Other forms needed in this process are described in

Form name: Responsive Declaration to Motion for Joinder and Consent Order of Joinder
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court if you agree with the request that a person be made a party in the family law case, as described in Notice of Motion and Declaration for Joinder (form FL-370).

Form name: Notice of Appearance and Response of Employee Benefit Plan
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: The employee benefit plan administrator uses this to respond to the the request to be joined in the family law case.

Form name: Summons (Joinder)
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells the administrators of an employee benefit plan that they are named as a claimant (a party) in a family law case and what will happen if a response is not filed in 30 days.

Form name: Application for Expedited Child Support Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the other parent that you want the court to order that parent to pay a specific amount of child support until trial. Tells you all other forms that are needed in this process.

Form name: Response to Application for Expedited Child Support Order and Notice of Hearing
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: The other parent responds to a request for an expedited chld support order. If applicable, includes details about a hearing before the court makes an order.

Form name: Expedited Child Support Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision (order) about a request for an expedited child support order.

Form name: Notice of Motion and Motion for Simplified Modification of Order for Child, Spousal, or Family Support
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the other parent (or party) details about a hearing to ask the court to change an order for child support, spousal or domestic partner support, or family support. Explains what other forms need to be complete and how to serve the documents on the other parent.

Form name: Information Sheet—Simplified Way to Change Child, Spousal, or Family Support
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explains how to use a simplified process to ask the court to change a child, spousal or domestic partner, or a family support order.

Form name: Responsive Declaration to Motion for Simplified Modification of Order for Child, Spousal, or Family Support
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court and the other party if you agree or disagree with the request to change a child support. spousal or domestic partner support, or family support order using a simplified process.

Form name: Information Sheet—How to Oppose a Request to Change Child, Spousal, or Family Support
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explains how to tell the court and the other parent (or party) that you disagree with the request to change orders for child, spousal or domestic partner, or family support.

Form name: Ex Parte Application for Restoration of Former Name After Entry of Judgment and Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court that a judgment for divorce or nullity was entered and now you want an order to let you legally use name you had before you married or registered the domestic partnership.

Form name: Request for Production of an Income and Expense Declaration After Judgment
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Ask the other party (your former spouse or domestic partner) to give you current financial information after the court entered a judgment in your case.

Form name: Request for Income and Benefit Information From Employer
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Ask the employer of your former spouse or domestic partner to give you information about employment status and wages if you did not receive a response using form FL-396 or the response received was incomplete.

Form name: Notice of Activation of Military Service and Deployment and Request to Modify a Support Order
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell that court and the other parent that you are a military service member, you have been activated to duty, deployed out of state, and you want to change a child support order.

Joint Petition for Summary Dissolution
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Start a simplifed process for divorce if you and your spouse or domestic partner have been married or partners for less than 5 years, do not own or owe very much, do not have children together, do not want spousal or partner support from each other, and you meet all other requirements listed in Summary Dissolution Information (form FL-810) to file this type of case.

Form name: Summary Dissolution Information
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explains who can use the simplified process to ask for a divorce, what forms you need to complete, and what steps you need to take to start and finish the case.

Form name: Request for Judgment, Judgment of Dissolution of Marriage, and Notice of Entry of Judgment
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court that you filed Joint Summary Dissolution (form FL-800) before January 1, 2011, and that you now want to finish the case.

Form name: Judgment of Dissolution and Notice of Entry of Judgment
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision in a summary dissolution case to end your marriage or domestic partnership. This states the date that you become single and tells each of you to comply with the agreement attached to the judgment.

Form name: Notice of Revocation of Joint Petition for Summary Dissolution
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court that you and your spouse or domestic partner want to stop the summary divorce process. This must be done within 6 months after you filed Joint Petition for Summary Dissolution (form FL-800) and other paperwork to start the case.

Form name: Request of Minor to Marry or Establish a Domestic Partnership
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court that you are under the age of 18 years and that you and your proposed spouse or domestic partner want a court order to allow you to marry or register a domestic partnership. Give information about your age, education,  and the written consent of each person's parents.

Form name: Order on Request of Minor to Marry or Establish a Domestic Partnership
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision (an order) on the minor's request to marry or register a domestic partnerthip. Includes information about that the court considered, the court's findings, a hearing, if any, and provides notices to the minor that are required by law.

Form name: Notice of Consolidation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells court clerks that the parties have multiple cases in family court, identifies the case number of each case, and combines those case under one primary case number.

Form name: Application and Order for Appointment of Guardian Ad Litem of Minor—Family Law
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court why you think the person you named should be appointed to speak on behalf of the child in the case. This includes a section for the person to consent to the appointment and a place for the court's findings and order.

Form name: Office of the Family Law Facilitator Disclosure
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells parties in a family law case that the Family Law Facilitator (FLF) is not their lawyers and that any communication with the FLF is not confidential.

Form name: Family Law Information Center Disclosure
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells parties in a family law case that staff at the court's Family Law Information Center (FLIC) are not their lawyers and that any communication with staff in the  is not confidential.

Form name: Notice of Limited Scope Representation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: The limited scope attorney tells the court and parties that the attorney will represent the client only on the issues and for the period of time specified in the notice.

Form name: Notice of Completion of Limited Scope Representation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: The limited scope attorney tells the court and all parties the date that the attorney completed the  agreed-upon tasks for the client. Also explains what the client must do in response to the notice.

Form name: Information for Client About Notice of Completion of Limited Scope Representation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Explains what to do if a client agrees or disagrees that the attorney finished the work that each  agreed would be completed in the family law case.

Form name: Objection to Application to Be Relieved as Counsel Upon Completion of Limited Scope Representation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court what services the limited scope attorney did not complete. Also, ask for a hearing and an order that the attorney to continue working on your case until the services are completed.

Form name: Response to Objection to Proposed Notice of Completion of Limited Scope Representation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: The limited scope attorney tells the court and the client what order the attorney is asking the court to make in response to client's Objection to Proposed Notice of Completion of Limited Scope Representation (form FL-956).

Form name: Order on Completion of Limited Scope Representation
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision (an order) after a hearing that the limited scope attorney did or did not finish the work that the attorney agreed to complete for the client.

Form name: Notice of Withdrawal of Attorney of Record
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tells the court the parties that the attorney is no longer representing a party in the case after the court entered a final judgment of divorce, legal sepration, or nullity.

Form name: Request and Declaration for Final Judgment of Dissolution of Marriage
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Ask the court to enter a judgment on the date when the judgment could have been originally signed, dated, and filed based on the facts of the case.

Form name: Application for Order for Publication or Posting
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Ask the court for an order to let you serve the summons in your case by publishing it a newspaper or posting it in a location where the other party will likely see it.

Form name: Order for Publication or Posting
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: States the court's decision (an order) that you can publish or post a summons in place of another type of legal service.

Form name: Proof of Service by Posting
Plain language description (1-2 sentence: Tell the court when and where the summons was posted and removed, and identifies the person who  papers.
